###First steps

After getting the code:

Replace your email settings in Application.properties
spring.mail.host = smtp.gmail.com
spring.mail.username = ************@gmail.com
spring.mail.password = *********

###Test samples

##Simple Mail without Attachments
curl --location --request POST 'http://localhost:8080/send-mail' \
--header 'accept: application/json' \
--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
--data-raw '    {
    "from" : "salvador.cadena@gmail.com",
    "to" : ["salvador.cadena@isol.com.mx"],
    "subject" : "Prueba",
    "body" : "body...."
    }
'

##Simple Mail with one Attachment


curl --location --request POST 'http://localhost:8080/send-mail-attachment' \
--header 'accept: application/json' \
--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
--data-raw '    {
    "from" : "salvador.cadena@gmail.com",
    "to" : ["salvador.cadena@isol.com.mx"],
    "subject" : "Prueba",
    "body" : "body....",
    "attachments" : [
        {
            "fileName" : "Calendario.pdf",
            "base64Content" : 
            ""
        }

    ]
    }
'
